      },
      "options": {
        "content": "## GatewayZ — LLM Streaming Performance\n\nTime-to-First-Chunk (TTFC), token throughput, and stream error analysis for AI streaming responses. Streaming quality directly impacts perceived user latency.\n\n| Signal | Target | What to Check |\n|--------|--------|---------------|\n| ⏱️ **TTFC P95** | < 3s | High TTFC = slow provider or long prompt queuing |\n| 🚀 **Token Throughput** | > 10 tokens/s | Drop = provider throttling or network congestion |\n| ❌ **Stream Errors** | < 2% | Broken streams = connection timeout or provider 5xx mid-stream |\n| 📡 **Active Streams** | < baseline × 2 | Spike = traffic burst; watch Redis connection count |\n\n_Metrics from Prometheus · Navigate: [Four Golden Signals](#) for overall error SLO · [AI Model Analytics](#) for per-model latency · [Infrastructure](#) for Redis health_",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "transparent": true,
      "pluginVersion": "11.5.2"
    },
